=============================================================================
Content-Centric Networking Skeleton - Implementation
=============================================================================

PARC's concept of Content-Centric Netwokring(CCN) is a promising idea. Still there 
are many challanges to face in this research area and PARC has done a great job
in this field with providing CCNx. However, we think that the research community
needs a more flexible and easily exentsible implementation of the CCN protocol.
Therefore we provide the Content-Centric Networking Sekleton(CCNs), which is an 
object oriented implementation of CCN. This implementation allows the research
community to easily integrate new ideas into the current CCN framework and to
evaluate them.


=============================================================================
Requirements
=============================================================================
* Ubuntu 12.04
* install qmake


=============================================================================
Build the Soruce Code
=============================================================================
* cd ccns/
* qmake
* make


=============================================================================
Clean the workspace
=============================================================================
* make clean
or
* make distclean


=============================================================================
Generate the Source Code Documentation
=============================================================================
* install Doxygen: sudo apt-get install doxygen
* cd ccns/
* doxygen ccns.doxygen
* documentation appears in ccns/doc/
